    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>TALK OF PRICE CONTROLS IN IRELAND</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Brian Lavery</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Lavery, Brian</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Inflation in Ireland reached annualized rate of 5.2 percent in May, a 15-year high and highest rate in European Union; government says it is considering how to address situation, including possibility of price controls (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Driven by increases in rent and house prices, Irish inflation reached an annualized rate of 5.2 percent in May, a 15-year high and the highest rate in the European Union. Trade unions said the new figures represented an ''inflation crisis'' that has erased worker income gains, and the Irish government said it was considering how to address the situation, including the possibility of price controls.</p>
        <p>Brian Lavery</p>
      </block>
